Before ajax request `div#goals_home_for` has a `p` tag inside it. And the `p` tag&#39;s style has `height: 40px`, so `div#goals_home_for` has 40px height. But after ajax request maybe your javascript edits DOM from response json data, and `div#goals_home_for` loses its child `p` tag. And it also loses its height.
Long story short, try:
```
#mainContent .fourthRow #goals_home_for {
   height: 40px;
   &lt;!-- Rest is omitted --&gt;
}
```
or edit your javascript so that it wraps `p` tags around each data.

