 1. Filling the form doesn&#39;t modify the html markup, nor will it change the `value` attribute in actual markup. So you can&#39;t get the value with `.innerHTML`. If you want the html with the new value just set the attribute to the new value.
 2. To make sure the script&#39;s output actually shows up in the other window, we should use `document.close()` after writing the content.

