You are storing the result of floating point computations in `int` arrays - that&#39;s a mistake, as warned by the compiler:

&gt; conversion from &#39;double&#39; to &#39;int&#39;, possible loss of data

Therefore an area of say `9.2` will not be considered smaller than `9.3` because they are both stored as `9`.

The arrays used during computation should be `double`. So the two arrays

    int area[n];
    int p[n];

should be
    
    double area[n];
    double p[n];

